<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The unit pivots today. From process to place.</p>
  <p>Blocks 1-4 taught the four surface-process domains as content: weathering, erosion, rivers, coasts. Today we pivot — what makes <strong>tropical, monsoon-dominated, coastal</strong> Chennai different from generic temperate-zone landscapes? Deep chemical weathering, lateritic soils, monsoon sediment pulses, anthropogenic modification at urban density: these aren't add-ons to the generic processes — they reshape them.</p>
  <p>Today is also the day the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">Landscape Reading</a> is assigned. You'll get the rubric walkthrough, the nine-location choice list, and the planning-audience framing. From this block forward, every U2 activity feeds the Reading.</p>
</section>

