<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Today is location-choice day. All four paths end with you having a top-3 list. The path you pick is about how you want to consider the options.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Walk the 9 cards (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Read all 9 location cards in the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">assessment handout</a>. For each, write one sentence on why it's interesting to YOU specifically. Then pick a top 3.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Source-test your top choice</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you already have a strong sense of your top location, source-test it now: in 25 minutes, find one government source, one news source, and one ambiguous source about it. Quick-OPVL each. If the source diversity is thin, swap to your #2.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-discuss with overlapping interest</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Find a partner with overlapping interest in 1-2 locations. Discuss what each of you would do differently with the same place. Useful for clarifying YOUR angle without copying someone else's.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Propose a non-listed location</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you have a personal connection to a non-listed place (your home village, a place you visit regularly, somewhere outside Chennai), draft a 1-paragraph proposal: where, why this is your place, what sources you'd use. Bring to Mr. Ignash for approval by Block 5.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

